cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SY. 

The paper is about population protocols, which are a model of distributed computation. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the correctness problem and computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper studies the expressive power of different classes of population protocols, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
